main event: A witness observed a bright, self-luminous, solid object with sharp edges in the sky over Cincinnati, Ohio on April 20, 1963.
interesting points: The object appeared to be about 20-30 feet in diameter and moved silently and rapidly in a west to east direction.
The witness showed the object to a friend, and they both watched it for about 30 seconds before it disappeared from view.
The object did not make any noise, give off any odor or heat, or have any effect on the witness, animals, or instruments in the vicinity.
The witness had not seen this or a similar phenomenon before, but reported the sighting to the Air Force.
Analysis by the Air Force indicated the witness was most likely observing the planet Jupiter.
sighted object: A bright, self-luminous, solid object with sharp edges
photographs: No photographs were included in the report
